-- Monti Says Italy Threatened by ‘Huge Possibility’ of Contagion
-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 2012-05-31T08:58:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/monti-says-italy-threatened-by-huge-possibility-of-contagion.html
Italy remains threatened by “huge
possibilities of contagion” even though its economic management
won a “fairly positive assessment” from the European
Commission yesterday, Prime Minister  Mario Monti  said.  “The spread as an indicator of contagion is there, is
there more for the overall weakness of the system,” Monti said
by video link to an EU conference in Brussels today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
